Key Features
✔ Family Doctor model—you choose a primary care physician
✔ Your family doctor coordinates your medical care and referrals
✔ 10%+ lower premiums compared to a free-choice model

How It Works
• You visit your chosen family doctor first for any medical needs.
• Your family doctor decides if you need to see a specialist.
• Standard benefits apply, and visits to gynecologists, eye doctors, and emergency rooms remain unrestricted.

Pros
✅ Cost savings due to coordinated care model
✅ Continuous care from a doctor who knows your medical history
✅ Strong CSS reputation for customer service

Cons
❌ You need a referral to see specialists outside your family doctor's practice
❌ Changing your family doctor mid-year requires approval
❌ Not ideal for those who want direct specialist access

Best for: Those who value a long-term relationship with their doctor and want to save money.
